OL,6,FThere's also an eye-catching increase
OL,7,Fto working age benefits.
OL,9,FMost of the extra #4 billion a year
OL,10,Fwould go on scrapping the two-child
OL,11,Flimit on benefits payments to
OL,12,Ffamilies. The benefits cap and the
OL,13,Fbedroom tax would also be ditched.
OL,15,FThe Archbishop of Canterbury has made
OL,16,Fthe compassionate case for ending and
OL,17,Fif you want to reduce child poverty,
OL,18,Fthen this would be a pretty targeted
OL,19,Fway of doing it, supporting poorer
OL,20,Ffamilies with three or more children.
