OL,3,CThe Lib Dem manifesto won't avoid
OL,4,Causterity in public services
OL,6,FThe Institute for Fiscal Studies
OL,7,F(IFS), The Resolution Foundation and
OL,8,Fthe National Institute for Economic
OL,9,Fand Social Research (NIESR) have been
OL,10,Fscreaming from the rooftops about the
OL,11,Fimplausibility of the existing
OL,12,Fspending plans beyond April next year.
OL,14,FThey say that if the next
OL,15,Fgovernmentthen it will have to either
OL,16,Fraise taxes or cut "unprotected" areas
OL,17,Fof public services by between #20-30
OL,18,Fbillion a year.
OL,20,FThat's a big hole and the Lib Dem
OL,21,Fmanifesto doesn't fill it.
