OL,3,CThe Lib Dem manifesto won't avoid
OL,4,Causterity in public services
OL,6,FArguably, it makes the hole bigger
OL,7,Fgiven the commitments the Lib Dems
OL,8,Fhave made on defence and overseas aid.
OL,10,FGiven that the party has ruled out
OL,11,Fincreases to income tax, national
OL,12,Finsurance and VAT then the chances are
OL,13,Fthat further austerity awaits.
OL,15,FAlthough, the party will keep the
OL,16,Fcurrent thresholds of income tax and
OL,17,Fnational insurance frozen until 2028 -
OL,18,Fa significant tax rise.
OL,20,FIn theory, is balanced. Extra spending
OL,21,Fis matched by extra revenue from tax.
